      "skill_tag": "arithmetic_sequences",
      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "body": "Find the common difference $d$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "attempt to use $u_4 = u_1 + 3d$, i.e. $19 = 7 + 3d$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$d = 4$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$d = 4$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** the fourth term is three steps beyond the first.$$u_4 = u_1 + 3d \\Rightarrow 19 = 7 + 3d$$$$3d = 12 \\Rightarrow d = 4$$So the common difference is $d = 4$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(7 + 3*4, 19)",
            "Eq(Rational(19 - 7, 3), 4)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Find $S_{12}$, the sum of the first 12 terms.",
          "marks": 3,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "substitute into $S_n = \\dfrac{n}{2}\\left(2u_1 + (n-1)d\\right)$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$S_{12} = 6(14 + 44)$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$S_{12} = 348$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$S_{12} = 348$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** use the arithmetic series formula (booklet).$$S_{12} = \\frac{12}{2}\\left(2(7) + 11(4)\\right) = 6(14 + 44)$$$$= 6 \\times 58 = 348$$So $S_{12} = 348$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(Rational(12, 2)*(2*7 + (12 - 1)*4), 348)",
            "Eq(Sum(7 + 4*(k - 1), (k, 1, 12)).doit(), 348)"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "An arithmetic sequence has first term $u_1 = 7$ and fourth term $u_4 = 19$."
    },
    {
      "source": "IB-AASL-P1-T1-Q2",
      "number": 2,
      "section": "A",
      "maximumMark": 5,
      "topic": "stats_probability",
      "skill_tag": "independent_events",
      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "body": "Find $P(A \\cap B)$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "use independence: $P(A \\cap B) = P(A)\\,P(B)$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$P(A \\cap B) = \\dfrac{1}{12}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$P(A \\cap B) = \\dfrac{1}{12}$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** for independent events the joint probability is the product.$$P(A \\cap B) = P(A)\\,P(B) = \\frac{1}{3} \\times \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{1}{12}$$So $P(A \\cap B) = \\dfrac{1}{12}$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(Rational(1, 3)*Rational(1, 4), Rational(1, 12))"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Find $P(A \\cup B)$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "use $P(A \\cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \\cap B)$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$P(A \\cup B) = \\dfrac{1}{2}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$P(A \\cup B) = \\dfrac{1}{2}$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** apply the addition rule (booklet).$$P(A \\cup B) = \\frac{1}{3} + \\frac{1}{4} - \\frac{1}{12} = \\frac{4 + 3 - 1}{12} = \\frac{6}{12} = \\frac{1}{2}$$So $P(A \\cup B) = \\dfrac{1}{2}$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(Rational(1, 3) + Rational(1, 4) - Rational(1, 12), Rational(1, 2))"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "c",
          "body": "Write down $P(A \\mid B)$.",
          "marks": 1,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$P(A \\mid B) = P(A) = \\dfrac{1}{3}$ (independence)"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$P(A \\mid B) = \\dfrac{1}{3}$",
          "solution": "Because $A$ and $B$ are independent, knowing $B$ has occurred does not change the probability of $A$:$$P(A \\mid B) = P(A) = \\frac{1}{3}$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(Rational(1, 12)/Rational(1, 4), Rational(1, 3))"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "Events $A$ and $B$ are independent, with $P(A) = \\dfrac{1}{3}$ and $P(B) = \\dfrac{1}{4}$."
    },
    {
