              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "expand the right-hand side: $2\\sin^2 x + 2\\sin x - \\sin x - 1$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "AG",
              "note": "$= 2\\sin^2 x + \\sin x - 1$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$(2\\sin x - 1)(\\sin x + 1) = 2\\sin^2 x + \\sin x - 1$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** expand the product and collect like terms.$$(2\\sin x - 1)(\\sin x + 1) = 2\\sin^2 x + 2\\sin x - \\sin x - 1$$$$= 2\\sin^2 x + \\sin x - 1$$which is the required expression.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(expand((2*sin(x) - 1)*(sin(x) + 1)), 2*sin(x)**2 + sin(x) - 1)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Hence solve $2\\sin^2 x + \\sin x - 1 = 0$ for $0 \\le x < 2\\pi$.",
          "marks": 4,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "$\\sin x = \\dfrac{1}{2}$ or $\\sin x = -1$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x = \\dfrac{\\pi}{6}$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x = \\dfrac{5\\pi}{6}$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x = \\dfrac{3\\pi}{2}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$x = \\dfrac{\\pi}{6},\\ \\dfrac{5\\pi}{6},\\ \\dfrac{3\\pi}{2}$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** use the factorisation from part (a).$$(2\\sin x - 1)(\\sin x + 1) = 0 \\Rightarrow \\sin x = \\frac{1}{2} \\text{ or } \\sin x = -1$$For $\\sin x = \\dfrac{1}{2}$ on $0 \\le x < 2\\pi$: $x = \\dfrac{\\pi}{6}$ and $x = \\pi - \\dfrac{\\pi}{6} = \\dfrac{5\\pi}{6}$. For $\\sin x = -1$: $x = \\dfrac{3\\pi}{2}$. The three solutions are $x = \\dfrac{\\pi}{6},\\ \\dfrac{5\\pi}{6},\\ \\dfrac{3\\pi}{2}$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(sin(pi/6), Rational(1, 2))",
            "Eq(sin(5*pi/6), Rational(1, 2))",
            "Eq(sin(3*pi/2), -1)",
            "Eq(2*sin(pi/6)**2 + sin(pi/6) - 1, 0)",
            "Eq(2*sin(3*pi/2)**2 + sin(3*pi/2) - 1, 0)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
