              "note": "$f^{-1}(x) = \\dfrac{x + 3}{x - 2}$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$f^{-1}(x) = \\dfrac{x + 3}{x - 2},\\ x \\ne 2$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** solve $y = f(x)$ for $x$.$$y = \\frac{2x + 3}{x - 1} \\Rightarrow y(x - 1) = 2x + 3$$$$xy - y = 2x + 3 \\Rightarrow xy - 2x = y + 3$$$$x(y - 2) = y + 3 \\Rightarrow x = \\frac{y + 3}{y - 2}$$Interchanging the variables, $f^{-1}(x) = \\dfrac{x + 3}{x - 2}$ (with $x \\ne 2$).",
          "verify": [
