          ],
          "answer": "$x = 3$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** combine the logs, solve the quadratic, then check the domain.$$\\log_3\\big(x(x - 2)\\big) = 1 \\Rightarrow x(x - 2) = 3$$$$x^2 - 2x - 3 = 0 \\Rightarrow (x - 3)(x + 1) = 0$$so $x = 3$ or $x = -1$. The original equation needs $x > 2$ for both logarithms to exist, so $x = -1$ is rejected. The solution is $x = 3$. Forgetting the domain check and giving both roots loses the final mark.",
          "verify": [
