              "note": "$2x = 3x - 3$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x = 3$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$x = 3$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** write both powers with base 2.$$4^x = (2^2)^x = 2^{2x}, \\qquad 8^{x-1} = (2^3)^{x-1} = 2^{3x - 3}$$Equating the exponents:$$2x = 3x - 3 \\Rightarrow x = 3$$Check: $4^3 = 64 = 8^2$. So $x = 3$.",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(4**3, 8**(3 - 1))",
            "solve(Eq(2*x, 3*x - 3), x) == [3]"
          ]
        }
      ]
